properties.headline: Small Craft Advisory issued February 13 at 3:40AM PST until February 14 at 10:00AM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Southwest winds 15 to 25 knots, becoming west to
northwest 20 to 30 kt in the afternoon. Seas 6 to 11 feet at
19 seconds.

* WHERE...Portions of Pacific coastal waters.

* WHEN...Until 10 AM PST Friday.

* IMPACTS...Conditions will be hazardous to small craft.
properties.instruction:
A Small Craft Advisory means that wind speeds of 21 to 33 knots
and/or seas 10 feet or higher are expected to produce hazardous
wave conditions to small craft. Inexperienced mariners,
especially those operating smaller vessels should avoid
navigating in these conditions.

NWSheadline: SMALL CRAFT ADVISORY NOW IN EFFECT UNTIL 10 AM PST FRIDAY
